parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to shut down, leaving the driver stranded, and in some cases, unable to open the doors or windows, posing a safety risk.
symptoms: The electrical system shuts down
the vehicle is dead
the battery is not dead but the electrical system shuts it down
the emergency key does not work to open the car
the vehicle requires a jump start or separation of the battery to reactivate the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The computer system or software issues can prevent the vehicle from being inspected, cause problems with the SYNC screen, and lead to safety issues if the vehicle's systems malfunction.
symptoms: The computer system does not allow an interface for inspection
the SYNC screen displays a blue or black image
the vehicle's computer system is unable to interface with the dealer's system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The damage to the wiring, particularly due to soy-based wire covering, can cause intermittent issues with the vehicle's systems, leading to safety risks if the vehicle's power shuts off while driving.
symptoms: The vehicle will intermittently not start
all dashboard lights flash
or the engine will turn off
the wiring is damaged by rats due to soy-based wire covering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of advanced safety features, such as the collision warning system, can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The alarm and lights flash to warn of an impending crash when there are no other vehicles on the road
the navigation system starts on its own giving directions to a location that was never entered previously into the system.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Deep Sleep Mode and Battery Drain
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deep sleep mode can cause the vehicle's battery to drain, leading to safety issues if the vehicle is unable to start or if the battery is dead.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into deep sleep mode after a period of inactivity
the remote features are disabled for battery optimization
the vehicle requires a jump start to turn on
the anti-lock brake fault is detected due to low battery
the pre-collision assist is not available due to a system fault or obstructed radar sensor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, as the driver may not have a clear view of the area behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear camera displays a blue screen
no rear video image is displayed
the camera fails to operate when engaged in reverse
warning messages of reverse brake assist unavailable
scattered screen
error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed Recall Repair for Back Over Prevention (NHTSA Campaign Number: 23V342000)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing the recall can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, as the vehicle may not have the necessary safety features to prevent accidents.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts are not available
manufacturer confirms parts are not available
dealer confirms parts are not available.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety features to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Back-up camera malfunctions
other electrical components fail
warning lights illuminate
rodents damage electrical wiring due to soy-based plastic covering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning 360 camera system can cause a delay or loss of rear camera visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions when reversing.
symptoms: Rear camera greyed out or not functioning when in reverse
CarPlay/iPhone is plugged in
lagging or delayed backup camera display
front camera displaying grey or blue image.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the panoramic sunroof can cause a loud noise, distractions, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from shattered glass.
symptoms: Loud noise
shattered glass
sunroof explosion
glass fragments falling into the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks can cause damage to the vehicle's interior, electrical systems, and create an environment conducive to mold growth, which can lead to health issues and unpleasant odors.
symptoms: Water leak evidence
mold growth on floor carpet and mat
musty odor
water damage around center console.
